description:
&lt;p&gt;If you are looking for challenge and change then come and join our newly integrated 0 – 19 Early Help Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In East Sussex we recognise the value of continuity of care and face to face visits in the home so you will manage a caseload within your locality team. Teams include Band 5 and Band 4 skill mix, delivering the Healthy Child Programme to children and families requiring various levels of intervention. We believe that the very best way to support our families is to support our staff so we offer high levels of supervision and staff support. We operate a transparent culture where we encourage innovative thinking and practice, we recognise that each family is unique and the service we provide accommodates families changing needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Relocation support available.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vacancies across all sites.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What we can offer you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supportive and accessible line-management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6 weekly 1-1 high quality clinical and safeguarding supervision from line managers who have undergone supervision training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8 weekly restorative group supervision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervision training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A programme of in-house clinical and professional development via conference style events, communities of practice and clinical update days&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consideration of other university modules based on how well they meet the needs of local families&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working as part of an integrated NHS-County Council team with access to good quality resources&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to a wide range of ESCC training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A workplace with a strong focus on staff wellbeing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development opportunities via delivery of clinical supervision and champion roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Involvement in service development and quality improvement via working groups, audit and feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Laptop enabled for agile working on a tailored case notes system and smart phones&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What we are looking for:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A fully qualified Health Visitor with a SCPHN degree&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SCPHN Students completing their training in August 2020 are welcome to apply&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A reflective and emotionally intelligent practitioner who makes good use of supervision and support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Someone who is able to address sensitive issues with families in a clear and supportive way&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Someone who demonstrates ESHT values in their interactions with all clients and colleagues: Respect and compassion, engagement and involvement, improvement and development and working together&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Someone who is able to prioritise their work based on need and have a clear rationale for every visit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to develop and maintain good interpersonal relationships with clients &amp; partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews will be held by Microsoft Teams &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
